This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with optical flow, disparity, and scene flow estimation using convolutional networks. The paper also mentions the use of synthetic datasets, which is a common approach in computer vision research. Additionally, the paper proposes a convolutional network for real-time disparity estimation, which is a popular topic in the computer vision community. The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it involves the use of supervised learning and convolutional networks. The Robotics (cs.RO) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories are also possible as the paper deals with scene flow estimation, which is relevant to both robotics and computer graphics.
